  "http://maven.apache.org/dtd/xdoc_1_0.dtd">

<document>
    <properties>
        <title>Forge Robots.txt - Installation</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Installation Instructions">
            <subsection name="Prerequisites">
                <p>
                    These instructions assume that you have a Hippo project based on the Hippo project archetype, i.e.
                    a Maven multiproject consisting of three submodules: cms, site and content.
                </p>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Installation">
                <ol>
                    <li>Set a version property in the root pom.xml of your project in the &lt;properties&gt; section:
                      <source><![CDATA[<forge.robotstxt.version>1.06.00</forge.robotstxt.version>]]></source>
                  </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Update the pom.xml of your <strong>CMS</strong> module to include the following dependency:</p>
                        <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.robotstxt</groupId>
  <artifactId>robotstxt-addon-repository</artifactId>
  <version>${forge.robotstxt.version}</version>
</dependency>]]></source>
                      <p>Note: before robotstxt version 1.04.00 the groupId was org.onehippo.forge</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Update the pom.xml of your <strong>site</strong> module to include the following dependency:</p>
                        <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.robotstxt</groupId>
  <artifactId>robotstxt-hst-client</artifactId>
  <version>${forge.robotstxt.version}</version>
</dependency>]]></source>
                      <p>Note: before robotstxt version 1.04.00 the groupId was org.onehippo.forge</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                     <p>Also in the <strong>site</strong> module, add the classpath of the robotstxt beans to the
                       'hst-beans-annotated-classes' context parameter in the web.xml</p>
                     <source><![CDATA[
<context-param>
  <param-name>hst-beans-annotated-classes</param-name>
  <param-value>
    classpath*:org/onehippo/cms7/hst/beans/**/*.class,
    classpath*:org/onehippo/forge/robotstxt/**/*.class
  </param-value>
</context-param>]]></source>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Rebuild your project using Maven. You should now be able to <a href="usage.html">
                            create the robots.txt document(s) in the CMS</a>.
                        </p>
                      <p><span class="note">Note:</span> on <strong>Hippo 7.8</strong> and later, be sure to use startup option <code>-Drepo.bootstrap=true</code>
                        for initializing the types, see
                        <a href="http://www.onehippo.org/7_8/library/concepts/content-repository/content-bootstrap.html">Content Bootstrap</a></p>
                    </li>
                </ol>

            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
